ğŸ” Day 1 Lab: Creating an AWS Key Pair
ğŸ“– Lab Explanation
This lab introduces you to creating an AWS Key Pair, which is your first step in working with AWS EC2 instances. Think of it as creating a secure digital key to access your cloud servers.

ğŸ” Key Terms Defined
Key Pair
What: A security credential consisting of two parts:

Public Key: Stored by AWS

Private Key: You download and keep secure

Purpose: Used instead of passwords for secure SSH access to EC2 instances

RSA (Rivestâ€“Shamirâ€“Adleman)
What: A widely used encryption algorithm

Purpose: Creates mathematically linked public and private keys

Alternative: ED25519 (newer, more efficient)

ğŸš€ Benefits & Why We Use Key Pairs
ğŸ”’ Security Advantages
More Secure than passwords (resistant to brute-force attacks)

No Password Sharing - private key never leaves your computer

Automatic Encryption - all communication is encrypted

ğŸ’¡ Practical Benefits
Required for SSH access to EC2 Linux instances

One-time Setup - create once, use for multiple instances

Easy Management - can be reused across instances

ğŸ¯ Use Cases
SSH Access to EC2 instances

Secure File Transfers

Automated Scripts accessing cloud resources

Disaster Recovery - having backup keys for critical instances

