Navigate to EC2 Service

Go to Services â†’ EC2

In left sidebar, find "Network & Security" â†’ "Key Pairs"

Create Key Pair

Click "Create key pair"

Name: datacenter-kp

Key pair type: RSA

Private key file format: .pem (for Linux/Mac) or .ppk (for Windows/PuTTY)

Click "Create key pair"

Download & Secure

The private key will automatically download

Important: Store it securely - you can't download it again!

Set proper permissions: chmod 400 datacenter-kp.pem

Method 2: AWS CLI (Alternative)
bash
aws ec2 create-key-pair --key-name datacenter-kp --key-type rsa --query 'KeyMaterial' --output text > datacenter-kp.pem
âš ï¸ Important Notes
